author: NEW YORK DAILY NEWS
title: Donald Trump Halloween costumes are trending on Google
text:
RICHARD DREW/AP Katie Couric once dressed up as Donald Trump for Halloween Donald Trump is top of the polls — the Halloween polls, that is.
Americans who want to dress up as the real estate mogul turned Republican presidential hopeful have sent Donald Trump Halloween costumes into trend mode on Google, the search engine giant reported Thursday.
Donald Trump is officially the top trending costume online nationwide, followed by Mal and Evie from the "Descendants" movie franchise, Marvel Comics’ Scarlet Witch and characters from Nickelodeon’s "PAW Patrol." Some old faithfuls also made the list, including Chewbacca from “Star Wars.”
Retailers have rushed to capitalize on the demand.
Risqué online costume and lingerie shop Yandy.com is selling a sexy costume named the "Donna T. Rumpshaker," for instance.
The limited-edition costume comes with a white sleeveless collared short, red tie, blue blazer and matching "booty shorts" - all for $69.95.
In Trump’s hometown of New York, costume shoppers have been going the more traditonal route, searching primarily for super hero outfits.
ANDREW KELLY/REUTERS Chewbacca costumes are also in high demand Bryan Pace for New York Daily News Kayla Ferguson as the Scarlet Witch at New York Comic Con Previous Next Enlarge The top searches in New York City are for Harley Quinn, the DC Comics character, Batman, Minnie Mouse and Catwoman, according to Google.
See below for a list of the top 10 trending searches nationwide.
1. Donald Trump
2. Mal (“Descendants” movie character)
3. Evie (“Descendants” movie character)
4. Scarlet Witch
5. PAW Patrol
6. Vision (Marvel character)
7. Wasp (Marvel character)
8. Chewbacca
9. Master Chief (“Halo” character)
10. R2-D2
